Common Cheating Issues and Solutions

We know cheats can cause problems not just in Emerald but also in many Pokemon games, including Pokemon ROM Hacks.

Unfortunately, some of these issues cannot be undone once you save your progress. However, there are ways to get rid of these problems, continue reading.

Shiny Pokemon Name Glitch

This is by far the most common issue for players who use the shiny cheat. The good news is that there’s a way to get rid of this problem, that’s simply by disabling the cheat before catching the shiny Pokemon. Here’s a complete guide we created on how to get rid of shiny Pokemon name glitches.

Bad egg

This is a fairly common problem when using the shiny cheat or the wild Pokemon encounter cheat. Do not save your progress after discovering a bag egg at your party to avoid this problem.

10 Interesting Facts About Earth's Oceans

But if it happens that you accidentally saved your progress, the only workaround is to deposit the bag of eggs in your box.

Bad eggs can repeatedly duplicate when you miss disabling the cheat that causes the bad egg, so it pays to disable any enabled cheats after use.

You can find more information about bad egg from this video.

Corrupted bag

This happens when using cheats like all tm/hm, all Pokeballs, all items, and other related cheats. The cheat will populate your bag with unusable items and will no longer make room for new items you get.

We don’t recommend these cheat; that’s why you can’t find them here.

Random restarts and freezing

This happens when two or more cheats are used simultaneously. Most of the time, pairing a cheat with another cheat rarely works. This can lead to random restarting and freezing; that’s why we always suggest using one cheat at a time.

Emulators that require adding “+” for spaces

We have received reports that the cheats are not working for some users. It’s important to note that certain GBA emulators have specific settings and may require adding a “+” instead of a space. For instance, in OpenEmu, you would enter BFF956FA+2F9EC50D to activate the rare candy cheat.

Delta Emulator for iOS users

To all iOS users who are using Delta Emulator, we are excited to share that cheats are fully functional in Pokemon Emerald. To apply the cheats, simply add the cheat code and choose the corresponding cheat type.

In the screenshot provided above, we are activating our all-time favorite cheat, the walk-through walls, with the cheat type Action Replay.

Please note: We use Emerald (U)(TrashMan) when testing the cheats. The cheats should also work on Pokemon Emerald v1.0 and other English versions of Pokemon Emerald.

Frequently Asked Questions

Why are Cheats Not Working?

There could be plenty of reasons a cheat cannot work; here is the list of fixes you can apply to address them.

First: Double check the cheat and remove empty spaces at the end of the code if there are any.

Second: As much as possible, use Emerald V1.0 as this version works best for cheats compared to V1.1.

Third: Are cheats not working on GBA4iOS? This is a common problem for most GBA4iOS users, and sadly, there’s no real fix for this problem yet.

Fourth: Select the correct cheat type. Some emulators, such as My Boy for Android, can detect the right cheat type, and we highly recommend using this app.

The fixes to common cheating problems are listed above. If the solutions listed do not work, you can watch this video guide.

How do you use Pokemon Emerald Cheats with My Boy’s free version?

If you are using the My Boy free version, you cannot use multiple-line cheats. To activate multiple-line cheats, you need the paid version of My Boy.

But there’s an easy trick to bypass this limitation. Enter the lines of codes as a separate cheat. That’s it!

How to use Pokemon Emerald Cheats with Visual Boy Advance (VBA) Emulator?

Step 1: Download the Visual Boy Advance version that fully supports cheats.
Step 2: Open VisualBoyAdvance.exe
Step 3: Click on “File”, click “Open” to select a ROM, and click on your Emerald ROM.
Step 4: Click on “Cheats” to show up the cheat list menu
Step 5: Select the appropriate cheat type (Gameshark or Code breaker)
Step 6: Click “OK” to activate the cheat.

How do you use Pokemon Emerald Cheats in Delta Emulator for iOS?

Adding Pokemon Emerald cheats to your Delta emulator is the same step as other emulators. However, make sure to add the cheat on its appropriate cheat type.

Conclusion

That concludes our list of Pokemon Emerald cheats and guides on how to use them. We hope you enjoy applying the above cheats. Cheating is surely fun, but use them with caution.

This is a friendly reminder not to overuse these cheats. Make sure to always disable or delete the cheat from the cheat list before saving your game progress. This will make sure the cheat is cleared in your settings.

Do you have any questions or suggestions, or have you discovered any cheats that you think should be added to the list above? Share them in the comment section below.
